    <div class=" text-left">
        <div class="bill-step">
            <div>1</div>
            <p>
                <strong>@Localizer["Payment Activity Notice"]</strong> - @Localizer["The Payment Activity Notice alerts taxpayers that our records"]
                @Localizer["reflect a penalty was imposed on the first installment of their property tax bill.  The penalty was imposed for one"]
                @Localizer["or more of the following reasons: no payment was received, a partial payment was received, or the first installment"]
                @Localizer["payment was received after the delinquency date."]
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bill-step">
            <div>2</div>
            <p>
                <strong>@Localizer["Assessor's Identification Number"]</strong> - @Localizer["This area identifies the Assessor’s Identification Number"]
                @Localizer["– (1234-567-890).  The Assessor’s Identification Number (AIN) is a ten-digit number assigned by the Office of the"]
                @Localizer["Assessor to each piece of real property in Los Angeles County.  This ten-digit AIN is made up of a four-digit Map"]
                @Localizer["Book Number (1234), a three-digit Page Number (567), and a three-digit Parcel Number (890)."]
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bill-step">
            <div>3</div>
            <p>
                <strong>@Localizer["Electronic Fund Transfer (EFT) Number"]</strong> - @Localizer["The EFT number is used to make credit card/Visa"]
                @Localizer["Debit card payments over the telephone.  To initiate a credit card/Visa Debit card payment, please call 1(888) 473-0835."]
                @Localizer["However, there are processing fees when paying by credit card/Visa Debit card.  Each transaction is limited to $99,999.99."]
                @Localizer["The PIN number is used to make electronic check payment to protect your security and privacy and is used to pay your current"]
                @Localizer["year and defaulted taxes online.  Effective with tax bills issued after August 2013, the PIN may contain all alpha, all numeric,"]
                @Localizer["or alpha/numeric characters.  The alpha letter 'O' is not used in the PIN.  The '0' is always a number zero."]
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bill-step">
            <div>4</div>
            <p><strong>@Localizer["Assessee"]</strong> - @Localizer["The owner of record and the mailing address on file with the Office of the Assessor."]</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bill-step">
            <div>5</div>
            <p>
                <strong>@Localizer["Special Information"]</strong> - @Localizer["This section provides important information about the bill"]
                @Localizer["and states whether there are any delinquent taxes owed."]
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bill-step">
            <div>6</div>
            <p>
                <strong>@Localizer["Assessor's Identification Number"]</strong> - @Localizer["This area identifies the Assessor’s Identification"]
